.TH "pci_scan_slot" 9 "pci_scan_slot" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_scan_slot \- Scan a PCI slot on a bus for devices
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pci_scan_slot
.BI "(struct pci_bus *bus "  ","
.BI "int devfn "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bus" 12
PCI bus to scan
.IP "devfn" 12
slot number to scan (must have zero function)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Scan a PCI slot on the specified PCI bus for devices, adding
discovered devices to the \fIbus->devices\fP list.  New devices
will not have is_added set.

Returns the number of new devices found.
